text:
Jennie Kim, also known as Jennie Kim (Hangul: 제니김, Hanja: 珍妮金, born January 16, 1996), commonly known as Jennie (Hangul: 제니) is a Korean female singer, songwriter, rapper, dancer, musician, fashion model, fashion icon, photographer, producer, director, and designer. She is a member of the girl group, Blackpink, founded and managed by YG Entertainment. At a young age, she went to New Zealand and stayed there for a period of time. She is most commonly known for her single ‘SOLO’.
Life.
Jennie was born on January 16, 1996 in Anyang, Gyeonggi, South Korea. She moved to New Zealand to live at age 8 and attended Waikowhai Elementary School as an exchange student.
In August 2010, she became a trainee of YG Entertainment.
Jennie is fluent in Korean, English and Japanese.
